title: Ziaullah Shah of PML-N wins PP-16 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Ziaullah Shah of the Pakistan Muslim League-Nawaz (PML-N) has won the election for Punjab Assembly constituency PP-16 Rawalpindi by securing 45478 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Ejaz Khan, an independent candidate who bagged 36402 votes.
Votersâ€™ turnout remained 41.8 percent.
